The Federal Executive Council (FEC), presided by President Muhammadu Buhari Wenesday approved the sum of N653.9million to procure and deploy hybrid spectrum monitoring system that will cover the southern part of the country, especially the South East. Briefing State House Correspondents after the 18th Virtual FEC meeting, in Abuja, the Minister of Communications and Digital Economy, Dr. Isa Pantami, said from the investigations carried out in five geo-political zones - North East, North west, North central, South west and South south, revealed that out of the 320 frequencies discovered, 106 were illegal. Pantami who noted the rampant use of illegal frequencies in the country, disclosed that based on the advise of the Attorney General and Minister of Justice, the illegal frequencies will be prosecuted.  The Minister of Transportation, Mr Rotimi Ameachi disclosed that the Council approved the award of contracts for the rehabilitation and reconstruction of the Port Harcourt-Maiduguri eastern narrow gauge railway, with new branch lines and trans-shipment facilities.  On his part, The Minister of Information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Mohammed on behalf of Ministers of Aviation and Works and Housing Ministers said FEC approved for the Ministries the rehabilitation of the various screening machines nationwide at the cost of N654 million and granted the completion of the rehabilitation of the Abeokuta-Ibadan road, a distance of 72 kilometers respectively.